import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='price', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of S&P 500 prices over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Price')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='price', kde=True, color='blue', bins=20)
    plt.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['price'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of S&P 500 prices?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Price")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month
    data['return'] = data['price'].pct_change()
    monthly_returns = data.groupby('month')['return'].mean()

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.barplot(x=monthly_returns.index, y=monthly_returns.values)
    plt.xlabel('Month')
    plt.ylabel('Average Monthly Return')
    plt.title('What is the average monthly return of S&P 500?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(y=monthly_returns.mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Return: {monthly_returns.mean():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='price', data=data, label='S&P 500 Price')
    
    std_dev = data['price'].std()
    mean_price = data['price'].mean()
    plt.fill_between(data['date'], mean_price - std_dev, mean_price + std_dev, color='b', alpha=0.2, label='1 Standard Deviation')
    
    plt.title('What is the volatility of S&P 500 prices?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Price')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
